Committee Report: Favorable
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: March 2, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Baltimore County Board of Education – Alterations of Elected Member Districts
3 and Establishment of Redistricting Process
4 FOR the purpose of requiring certain members of the Baltimore County Board of Education
5 to be elected in a certain manner from certain districts in certain elections; requiring
6 the chair of the Baltimore County delegation to the General Assembly to introduce
7 legislation to reapportion certain school board districts in a certain manner after
8 each decennial census of the United States; and generally relating to elected member
9 districts for the Baltimore County Board of Education.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
11 Article – Education
12 Section 3–2B–01
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 BY adding to
16 Article – Education
17 Section 3–2B–11
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
19 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
20 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
21 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0040*

2 SENATE BILL 40
1 Article – Education
2 3–2B–01.
3 (a) The Baltimore County Board of Education consists of:
4 (1) Seven nonpartisan elected members;
5 (2) Four appointed members; and
6 (3) One student member.
7 (b) (1) Of the 11 elected and appointed members of the county board:
8 (i) 1. [One] BEFORE THE 2034 GENERAL ELECTION, ONE
9 member shall be elected from each of the seven councilmanic districts in the county,
10 established by the County Council of Baltimore County IN EXISTENCE ON OCTOBER 1,
11 2024, by the voters of that district; and
12 2. BEGINNING WITH THE 2034 GENERAL ELECTION, ONE
13 MEMBER SHALL BE ELECTED FROM EACH OF THE SEVEN SCHOOL BOARD DISTRICTS
14 ESTABLISHED BY THE REDISTRICTING PROCESS DESCRIBED IN § 3–2B–11 OF THIS
15 SUBTITLE, BY THE VOTERS OF THAT DISTRICT; AND
16 (ii) Four members shall be appointed by the Governor from the
17 county at large.
18 (2) (i) The seven elected members shall be elected at a general election
19 in gubernatorial election years in accordance with § 3–2B–02 of this subtitle.
20 (ii) The four appointed members shall be appointed by the Governor
21 in presidential election years from a list of nominees submitted by the Baltimore County
22 School Board Nominating Commission as provided in § 3–2B–03 of this subtitle:
23 1. On the expiration of the term of an incumbent appointed
24 member within 30 days after the general election; or
25 2. Within the 30–day period otherwise required under this
26 subtitle.
27 (3) (i) A member from a school board district shall be at least 21 years
28 old, a resident of that district for at least 2 years, and a registered voter of the county before
29 the election.

SENATE BILL 40 3
1 (ii) A member from a district who does not maintain residency in
2 that district may not continue as a member of the county board and the office shall be
3 deemed vacant.
4 (iii) If the boundary line of a district is changed, the term of an
5 incumbent member of the county board who no longer resides in the district because of the
6 change is not affected during this term.
7 (4) (i) A member may not be elected or appointed to serve on the county
8 board for more than three consecutive terms.
9 (ii) A member who has served three consecutive 4–year terms may
10 not be elected or appointed to the county board until at least 4 years have elapsed since the
11 end of the member’s last term on the county board.
12 (5) During an election year:
13 (i) The Governor may not appoint as a member of the county board
14 an individual who files a certificate of candidacy for election to the county board; and
15 (ii) An individual who files a certificate of candidacy for election to
16 the county board may not seek appointment to the county board by the Governor through
17 nomination by the Baltimore County School Board Nominating Commission.
18 3–2B–11.
19 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “SCHOOL BOARD DISTRICT” MEANS THE GEOGRAPHIC
20 AREA OF BALTIMORE COUNTY FROM WHICH AN ELECTED MEMBER OF THE
21 BALTIMORE COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION IS ELECTED.
22 (B) (1) BEGINNING AFTER THE 2030 U.S. CENSUS, THE SCHOOL BOARD
23 DISTRICTS SHALL BE:
24 (I) REAPPORTIONED AFTER EACH DECENNIAL CENSUS OF THE
25 UNITED STATES; AND
26 (II) EFFECTIVE FOR EACH GENERAL ELECTION WHERE A
27 MEMBER WILL BE ELECTED UNTIL THE FOLLOWING DECENNIAL CENSUS.
28 (2) THE REAPPORTIONED SCHOOL BOARD DISTRICTS UNDER THIS
29 SECTION SHALL BE SUBSTANTIALLY EQUAL IN POPULATION.
30 (C) AFTER EACH DECENNIAL CENSUS, THE CHAIR OF THE BALTIMORE
31 COUNTY DELEGATION TO THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY SHALL INTRODUCE
32 LEGISLATION TO REAPPORTION THE SCHOOL BOARD DISTRICTS.

4 SENATE BILL 40
1 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act is an emergency
2 measure, is necessary for the immediate preservation of the public health or safety, has
3 been passed by a yea and nay vote supported by three–fifths of all the members elected to
4 each of the two Houses of the General Assembly, and shall take effect from the date it is
5 enacted.
Approved:
